From: Custom Buildroot User
Subject: ASoC: sunxi: sun4i-i2s: Limit DMA maxburst to 4 for F1C100s

The F1C100s (suniv) DMA controller strictly supports a maximum burst
size of 4 words. The default sun4i-a10-i2s configuration requests a 
burst size of 8, which causes a DMA channel allocation failure 
(-ENOMEM) during the ALSA trigger phase.

This patch limits the maxburst to 4 to prevent bus faults and enable
successful I2S audio playback on the F1C100s.

---
 sound/soc/sunxi/sun4i-i2s.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/sound/soc/sunxi/sun4i-i2s.c b/sound/soc/sunxi/sun4i-i2s.c
--- a/sound/soc/sunxi/sun4i-i2s.c
+++ b/sound/soc/sunxi/sun4i-i2s.c
@@ -1341,10 +1341,10 @@ static int sun4i_i2s_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 
 	i2s->playback_dma_data.addr = res->start +
 					i2s->variant->reg_offset_txdata;
-	i2s->playback_dma_data.maxburst = 8;
+	i2s->playback_dma_data.maxburst = 4;
 
 	i2s->capture_dma_data.addr = res->start + SUN4I_I2S_FIFO_RX_REG;
-	i2s->capture_dma_data.maxburst = 8;
+	i2s->capture_dma_data.maxburst = 4;
 
 	dev_set_drvdata(&pdev->dev, i2s);